# Trivy vulnerability suppressions.
#
# The entries below are transitive CVEs that live entirely inside the
# @earendil-works/pi-* host-platform peer-dependency subtree. Per AGENTS.md,
# those host packages are never direct dependencies of this extension: they are
# provided by the Pi host at runtime and are not part of this package's
# published `files`. The affected versions are pinned inside the peer subtree
# (marked `peer: true` in package-lock.json) and cannot be reliably replaced via
# npm `overrides` without force-bumping the host platform packages themselves, so
# they are suppressed here with justification rather than patched locally.

# brace-expansion 5.0.6 (via @earendil-works/pi-coding-agent > minimatch):
# DoS via exponential-time expansion. Reached only by the host toolchain, not
# shipped by this extension.
CVE-2026-13149

# protobufjs 7.6.4 (via @earendil-works/pi-* > @google/genai):
# DoS via infinite loop in .proto option parsing. Reached only by the host
# platform's AI stack, not shipped by this extension.
CVE-2026-59877
